cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.AI, cs.GT

This paper deals with privacy concerns in incentivizing passengers to switch from private to public transit services to mitigate traffic congestion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes algorithms to solve the problem, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper uses differential privacy, which is a technique used in privacy-preserving data analysis, and thus, it could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also formulates the problem as a mixed integer linear program and a convex program, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), respectively.
